column4: <content>65. Eislauf beim Georgtor. 78. Mention at end that as proved by Glück done after drawing.</content>

<parts.title>[Addendum] 109. Witt Library. P.B.II. Rent Day: 1) A Tooth, [?] 1928, then Curtis Sale (anonymous coll.) Christie, 9-VII-1937, N° 130. Signed and dated 1621, panel 281/2 x 47in. On mount: 29 x48 1/2 in. Lord Walter Talbot Kerr Coll. Hatfield. Bought by [?]; 2) Sale Herele, Antwerp, 30-31-V-1938, N° 24, Bois, 58 x 93 cm.</parts.title>
<parts.title>Ad [Addendum] 109. Rijksbureau. Rent Day. Antwerp, Cat. 1920, N° 646.Dazu in Rijksbureau noch neun Wiederhohlungen.</parts.title>

<parts.title>[Addendum] 109. Sale Christie, Manson & Co, July 10, 1953. Different Properties P.BRVEGHEL. 86. RENT DAY-signed and dated 1560 (sic!) - on panel 211/2 x35in. From the collection of the late T.W. Swart, Esq. of Sydney, Australia, who is said to have purchased it at the Northwick Sale in 1859; [toegevoegde vermelding]: 'F.G. A rather good version. Signed and dated: P.BREVGHEL 1562.'</parts.title>

<parts.title>[recto][Addendum] 109. Witt Library. Interior P.B.I Box 5-'Chez l'Avocat'-Rent Day: 1) Apple by Brother, (Phot London 1949); 2) Kaven Sale, Berlin, Lepke, 22-III-1917, N° 117 Art des [sic] P.B.I, Holz 73 x 104; 3) Antwerp Mus. Grebens Legacy: 'Title'; 4) Elsne Sale, Keller & Reiner, Berlin, 13-II-1913, N° 17, Holz, parettiert, 51 x 83 cm; 5) Schropp Sale, Nice, 27-XI-1933, 5. Panneau parquetté, 56 x86 cm; 6) Photogr. Squerreys Court, Westerham; 7) Permannet Collection Carnegie Institute, Pittsburgh, Pennsylvania. Signed 'P. Breugel 1560.'; [verso] Sale Schidlof, Vienna, 4-6-II-1920, N° 16 as 'Hollandische Schule, 17. Jhdt., Lwd. 76 x 117. Now in ....[sic] Coll. Adelaide.</parts.title>
<parts.title>Ad [Addendum] 65. Eislauf vor dem Georgstor. Die zeichnung ist in Privatbesitz in U.S.A. [...]</parts.title>

<parts.title>Witt Library. M. van Cleve. Eislauf vor Georgstor mit Tor rechts. P. de Boer, Amsterdam 1938, N° 11 Maerten van Cleve, Bois 106x148 cm (Vorher bei B. Doehler, Munich 1926; 1949 bei Böhlen Luzern ([?] von Glück: paint par M. van Cleve d'après un dessin de P.B.I, d'après lequel aussi la gravure Bastelaer 205; [Notitie FG]: 'To be added at end.'</parts.title>
<parts.title>Alt 65. Bruegel: Eislauf vor Georgstor. Zeichnung in amerik. Privatbesitz. Ges. Photographie Anfang Juli 1950 bei Herbert Bier [...]</parts.title>
